<p itemprop="description">A lead interaction designer leads the interaction design function across the organisation, setting strategic direction for user experience approaches and ensuring user-centred design principles are embedded throughout all digital services. They manage interaction design teams and drive organisational UX excellence.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define and implement interaction design strategy across the entire organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead and manage interaction design teams and UX specialists</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish interaction design governance, standards, and design systems</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Champion user-centred design approaches at executive level</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build strategic partnerships with design and UX communities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Oversee UX capability development and training programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in interaction design tools, techniques, and methodologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure user experience excellence across all organisational programmes</li>
    </ul>
</section>

